article.headline: New Hampshire 75, Binghamton 72
article.story: BINGHAMTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Blagoj Janev scored 18 points to lead New Hampshire in a 75-72 win over Binghamton Thursday. Tyrece Gibbs scored 16 points and Jermaine Anderson contributed 15 for New Hampshire (7-12, 3-3 America East) Mike Gordon scored 20 points to lead Binghamton (9-10, 2-5). Steve Proctor added 16 and Lazar Trifunovic had 11 points. Binghamton led 36-30 at the end of the first half. New Hampshire outrebounded Binghamton 30-23.
